<item>
            <title>[WFLY-7105] Incorrect redirection after authentization when using elytron</title>
                <link>https://issues.jboss.org/browse/WFLY-7105</link>
                <project id="12313721" key="WFLY">WildFly</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Having web application which uses defined security domain, which is set up using elytron results in incorrect redirection. It is redirecting after authentication done at &lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://localhost:8080/defined-security-domain/user/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://localhost:8080/defined-security-domain/user/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/tt&gt; to &lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://localhost:8080/defined-security-domain/user//user/index.jsp&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://localhost:8080/defined-security-domain/user//user/index.jsp&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/tt&gt; instead of to &lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://localhost:8080/defined-security-domain/user/index.jsp&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://localhost:8080/defined-security-domain/user/index.jsp&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note, when using only old security domain setup without elytron, it works just fine.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
